## Phase5 — Flexible Orientation Transitions ✅

**Goal:** Correct behavior when user rotates between screens; stable gameplay during a match.

### Decision (revised)

Initial approach: debounced mid-game restart (`resetActiveGame`) on orientation change. **Device QA failed** — paddles kept portrait Y positions in landscape, ball could disappear, layout loops caused "Maximum update depth exceeded".

**Current approach:** Lock orientation for the duration of an active match. Free rotation on intro and win screens only.

### Intro / win rotation flow

```
orientation change (!gameStarted || winner !== null)
  → useLayoutEffect:
      isPortraitSV updated
      setCourtBounds(null)   // avoid stale overlay frame
  → court onLayout:
      updateCourtBounds (guarded)
      syncCourtMetrics + positionPaddles
  → portrait: overlay reframes via CourtOverlayFrame + courtBounds
  → landscape: fullScreenOverlay on playArea (centered Start/Win/Pause; compact layout)
  → court key={portrait|landscape} forces remeasure on orientation flip
```

### Active play flow

```
gameStarted && !winner
  → lockedGameplayPortrait set in startGame / playAgain
  → useGameplayOrientationLock(lockedPortrait):
      lockAsync(PORTRAIT_UP | LANDSCAPE)
      accelerometer baseline tilt (normalized gravity angle via expo-sensors)
      + Dimensions / ScreenOrientation listeners as fallback
  → on physical rotate (~32° from baseline) or UI dimension mismatch:
      RotationLockedBanner (4s, safe-area bottom padding)
      isPaused = true (auto-resume when banner dismisses)
      haptic warning; re-lock orientation
  → on unlock: intro screen or win overlay
```

### Done

- [x] Layout switch without remounting `GameScreen`
- [x] `CourtOverlayFrame` — portrait start/win/pause overlays match court bounds
- [x] Landscape menus use `fullScreenOverlay` (not court bounds — fixes intro rotate layout)
- [x] `StartOverlay` / `WinOverlay` / `PauseOverlay` extracted; `compact` prop for landscape
- [x] Portrait HUD visible during overlays (not covered)
- [x] `courtBounds` tracked from court `onLayout`; cleared on orientation change
- [x] `lockedGameplayPortrait` captured at `startGame` / `playAgain`; cleared when match ends
- [x] Court `key={portrait|landscape}` forces layout remeasure on orientation flip
- [x] Gameplay entities hidden under overlays (no paddle/scoreboard bleed-through)
- [x] `ensurePrimaryBall()` — ball entry always exists before `launchBall`
- [x] Mid-game orientation **lock** replaces debounced restart
- [x] `RotationLockedBanner` for rotation-blocked feedback (replaces `GameToast`)
- [x] `expo-sensors` accelerometer — normalized gravity tilt detect (works in g and m/s²)
- [x] Rotation banner auto-pauses; auto-resumes on dismiss; suppresses `PauseOverlay`
- [x] Removed `resetActiveGame` / `scheduleOrientationReset` mid-game path

### Rotation smoke-test checklist

| State | Rotate portrait ↔ landscape | Expected |
|-------|------------------------------|----------|
| Pre-game (start overlay) | Either direction | Portrait: court-framed overlay. Landscape: centered full-screen menu |
| Mid-game | Either direction | Device stays locked; gold banner + brief pause on physical rotate; paddles/ball unaffected |
| Paused | Either direction | Same as mid-game (still locked) |
| Won (play again overlay) | Either direction | Unlocked; overlay reframes; scores unchanged |
| Cold start landscape → play | N/A | Paddles left/right, vertically centered; ball launches on paddle |
| Landscape intro | Rotate to landscape | Start menu centered (not clipped to bottom court bounds) |

### Native rebuild required

`expo-screen-orientation` and `expo-sensors` are native modules. After pulling changes:

```bash
npx expo run:ios
# or
npx expo run:android
```

Hot reload alone does not apply orientation lock or accelerometer.

**Android clean builds:** avoid `cd android && ./gradlew clean` (CMake/codegen race on new arch). Prefer:

```bash
rm -rf android/app/.cxx android/app/build android/build
npx expo run:android
```

