## Phase7 — Court Entities (Powerups & Stones) ✅

**Goal:** Readable powerup feedback and dynamic court obstacles.

### Powerups — labeled icons

- [x] Replace color-only orbs with first-letter labels (`G` / `S`) via `Powerup.tsx`
- [x] `POWERUP_LABELS` + `POWERUP_COLORS` in `game.ts`
- [x] Ball collision + tap both apply effect to court-half owner (AI or You)
- [x] Grow / shrink paddle height for 5s (scaled base height from `courtMetrics`)

### Stones — random obstacles

- [x] `Stone.tsx` — gray rocky circles on court
- [x] `generateCourtStones()` in `stones.ts` — random count (3–4) and positions
- [x] Placement avoids paddle zones and stone overlap (rejection sampling)
- [x] `resolveStoneCollisions()` in `ballPhysics.ts` — UI-thread circle bounce
- [x] Regenerate on **Start** / **Play Again**; stable during active rally (not on every layout)

### Ball speed fix (stone interaction)

Paddle hits previously used only `|vx|` (landscape) or `|vy|` (portrait). After a stone deflection, most speed could sit on the other axis — the next paddle hit then reset the ball to near-crawl speed.

- [x] `nextPaddleHitSpeed()` uses `Math.hypot(vx, vy)` for paddle rebound speed
- [x] `resolveStoneCollisions()` enforces minimum speed (`initialBallSpeed × 0.55`) after stone bounce

Note: center court still has intentional **0.75×** travel speed on the primary axis (`zoneMult` in `ballPhysics.ts`, middle 30% of court).

### Stone tuning (`game.ts`)

| Constant | Value |
|----------|-------|
| `STONE_RADIUS_BASE` | 16 px (scaled by court) |
| `STONE_COUNT_MIN` | 3 |
| `STONE_COUNT_MAX` | 4 |

